        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 5:09PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 509 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Avondale, or 12 miles southeast of Pueblo Airport, moving east at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Avondale.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
